---
title: Honey Miso Chicken & ’Shroom Jumble over Lime Rice with Sweet Potatoes, Zucchini & Creamy Chili Sauce
description: Craving a jumble of roasted veggies for dinner? We’ve got just the thing. Here, we roast sweet potato, mushrooms, onion, and zucchini until tender, then toss with a ginger-infused honey miso dressing for sweet and savory flavor. The veggies are all piled over buttery lime rice, then drizzled with a creamy chili sauce for a little heat and sprinkled with sesame seeds for crunch. Hearty, saucy, and oh-so satisfying—it doesn’t get any better than that.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/642307cdd7a841004e000267-159ed43a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65a8158b4bb81dc143a6dbb1.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-miso-chicken-and-shroom-jumble-65a8158b4bb81dc143a6dbb1
time required: 45 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 1080 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 115 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 660 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
---

Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{2%unit}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Trim and halve @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and halved). Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1%unit}(peeled and cut into ½-inch-thick wedges). Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit}. Peel and grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss sweet potato, mushrooms, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining Fry Seasoning in the next step.)

Roast on middle rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll start the zucchini then).

Meanwhile, toss zucchini on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, remaining @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, and @salt{}.

Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, place sheet with zucchini on top rack. Roast until everything is browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @honey{2%tsp}, @miso sauce concentrate{1%unit}, a big squeeze of lime juice, and ginger to taste.

In a separate small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Once veggies and zucchini are done, combine on a baking sheet and toss with honey-miso dressing.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{}.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with sweet potato and mushroom jumble. Drizzle with creamy chili sauce and sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise. Top rice with chicken along with sweet potato and mushroom jumble.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.